## Testing

- Write unit tests with **Vitest** for stores, utilities, and pure functions.
- Write component tests with **@testing-library/svelte**.
- Place test files alongside source files as `*.test.ts` or in a `/tests/` directory.
- Aim for **>80% coverage** on stores and utility functions.
- Test user interactions (clicks, inputs) not implementation details.

```ts
// counter.test.ts
import { get } from 'svelte/store';
import { count } from './counter';

test('increments correctly', () => {
  count.set(0);
  count.update((n) => n + 1);
  expect(get(count)).toBe(1);
});
```

### E2E Testing
- Use **Playwright** for end-to-end tests.
- Store E2E tests in `/e2e/` directory.
- Test critical user flows (auth, checkout, navigation) end-to-end.

---

## Documentation

- Every component should have a brief comment block describing its purpose and props.
- Document stores with JSDoc comments explaining the shape and intent.
- Use `README.md` files in major directories (`/stores`, `/lib`, `/routes`) to describe conventions.
- Keep a root `ARCHITECTURE.md` describing the folder structure and key decisions.

```svelte
<!--
  @component UserCard
  Displays a user's avatar, name, and role badge.

  Props:
  - name: string — Full display name
  - role: 'admin' | 'user' — Determines badge color
  - avatarUrl?: string — Optional profile image URL
-->
```

---

## File & Folder Structure

```
src/
├── lib/
│   ├── components/      # Reusable UI components
│   ├── types/           # Shared TypeScript interfaces
│   └── utils/           # Pure utility functions
├── routes/              # SvelteKit pages and layouts
├── stores/              # Svelte writable/derived stores
└── app.html             # Root HTML shell
```

---

## Naming Conventions

| Thing            | Convention                  | Example                    |
|------------------|-----------------------------|----------------------------|
| Components       | PascalCase                  | `UserCard.svelte`          |
| Stores           | camelCase                   | `userStore.ts`             |
| Utility files    | camelCase                   | `formatDate.ts`            |
| Route files      | SvelteKit conventions       | `+page.svelte`             |
| CSS classes      | kebab-case                  | `.card-header`             |
| TypeScript types | PascalCase                  | `UserProfile`              |
| Constants        | SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE        | `MAX_RETRIES`              |

---

## CSS & Styling

- Use **scoped `<style>` blocks** in components by default — avoid global styles unless necessary.
- Place truly global styles in `/src/app.css` only.
- Use **CSS custom properties** (variables) for theming; define them in `:root`.
- Prefer utility classes (Tailwind) or scoped styles — avoid inline `style=` attributes.
- Keep animation/transition logic in Svelte transitions (`transition:`, `animate:`) rather than raw CSS keyframes where possible.

---

## Don'ts

- ❌ Don't use `document` or `window` directly in components — gate with `browser` check from `$app/environment`.
- ❌ Don't fetch data in `onMount` for initial page data — use `load()`.
- ❌ Don't commit `.env` files — use `.env.example` with placeholder values.
- ❌ Don't use `any` type in TypeScript.
- ❌ Don't leave `console.log` statements in production code.
- ❌ Don't use deprecated Svelte 4 APIs if on Svelte 5 (e.g., use runes `$state`, `$props` where applicable).
